      "writtenOn": "2021-02-11T18:49:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yeah, we definitely could do that, and I considered that here, but I\u0027ve yet to think of any situation where transforming from A -\u003e B -\u003e C where A!\u003dC would make any sense.  I think the sandwich will prevent more accidental errors than interesting use cases.\n\nI could see maybe hypothetically someone might want to write effects that work as if A -\u003e B -\u003e C -\u003e A, where B -\u003e C happens all inside the effect itself.  But I haven\u0027t run into one of those yet.  Tying the input and output formats actually kind of makes writing shaders easier, and that\u0027s how things work today, just with a fixed \u0027A\u0027 instead of user-defined \u0027B\u0027.",
